<div class="jumbotron text-center">
  <h1>Nepal</h1> 	 
	<p>Taste of Nepal Tour is designed to take you to places where you can enjoy most spectacular mountain views, historical monuments, traditional Hindu and Buddhist Temples and also experience a wonderful, Nepalese hospitality in the remote areas.
	</p>
	<div class="container">
	<h1>Itinerary</h1>
<pre><p><h2>Day 1</h2>- On your arrival in  Kathmandu International airport,our representative
 will meet you and drive to the hotel.Kathmandu is an old city known for its cultural and 
 architectural heritage.</p>

<p><h2>Day 2</h2>- The very next morning, after breakfast you will leave for a full day 
sightseeing tour around Kathmandu valley. You can visit sacred Pashupatinath Temple and 
Swyambhunath,very ancient and essentially enlisted in UNESCO World Heritage sites. </p>

<p><h2>Day 3</h2>- After breakfast  drive on to Chitwan National Park, about 5 hour deriver 
through scenic high way, on arrival at resort lunch will served and our nature guide will brief
 you about the programme. Wildlife in Chitwan National Park includes the greater one-horned 
 rhinoceros, spotted deer, hog deer, sambar deer and barking deer as well as a wide variety of birdlife. 
</p>

<p><h2>Day 4</h2>- Transfer to airport to fly back to the onward destination.</p>
</pre>

<h3> Ready for the trip?</h3>
<a href="book.html" class="btn btn-info" role="button">Book Now</a>


